Reasoning: The paper discusses distributed data processing platforms for cloud computing, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on data science and big data analysis suggests cs.DB (databases) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) as likely categories. The comparison of different platforms and their usability suggests cs.SE (software engineering) as another possible category. The use of machine learning techniques for data analysis could also place the paper in cs.LG (machine learning) or cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing).
